  <prompt>
    Author a new `sprk_chartdefinition` Dataverse record named `Matter Next Date` per FR-DV-04. Visual Type = `DueDateCard` (100000008) — no renderer changes required (DueDateCard exists today). Entity = `sprk_event`. Data via FetchXML: TOP 1 ORDER BY `finalduedate ASC` WHERE `regardingmatter = @currentMatter AND finalduedate ≥ today`. Configure Drill Through to `sprk_event` filtered to upcoming for current matter. Verify the chart renders date + event title + days-from-now (e.g., `May 28 / Pre-trial hearing · in 3d`) on a Matter with an upcoming event.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Dataverse configurator with familiarity with the Visual Host chart-definition contract, the existing `DueDateCard` visual type, and FetchXML TOP-N queries. Comfortable using the Dataverse MCP (`create_record` / `read_query`) or PowerShell + Web API.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A single `sprk_chartdefinition` record exists in Dataverse named `Matter Next Date` with Visual Type = DueDateCard (100000008) and a FetchXML TOP 1 query returning the next upcoming `sprk_event`. Drill Through goes to `sprk_event` filtered to upcoming for current matter. A test Visual Host instance bound to this chart def renders date + event title + days-from-now matching the existing DueDateCard contract.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-DV-04 is the simplest chart def in this project — it reuses the existing `DueDateCard` visual type with no renderer changes. The only dependency is task 003 (sprk_event field verification). Per §6.4.0 (binding), this MUST use the existing DueDateCard visual type only; no new options, no Matter-specific code paths. The card's display contract (date + title + days-from-now) is already defined by DueDateCard.tsx — author the record to feed it the right data.
    </background>
