  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `projects/spaarke-matter-ui-enhancement-r1/notes/spikes/sprk_event-field-verification.md` (task 003 output) to confirm the verified schema field names for `regardingmatter`, `finalduedate`, and the event-title display field on `sprk_event`. Use those verified names in the FetchXML below.</step>
    <step order="2">Read `src/client/pcf/VisualHost/control/components/DueDateCard.tsx` to confirm the expected data-binding shape (which field provides date, which provides title, and how `days-from-now` is computed). DO NOT modify the component.</step>
    <step order="3">Construct the FetchXML TOP 1 query: ORDER BY `finalduedate ASC` WHERE `regardingmatter = @currentMatter AND finalduedate ≥ today`. Return the event with its `finalduedate` and title-display field for DueDateCard consumption. Use verified field names from step 1.</step>
    <step order="4">Author the `sprk_chartdefinition` record using mcp__dataverse__create_record. Fields: `sprk_name` = "Matter Next Date", `sprk_visualtype` = 100000008, `sprk_entityname` = "sprk_event", `sprk_datafetchxml` (or equivalent) = the FetchXML from step 3, drill-through entity = `sprk_event`, drill-through filter = upcoming for current matter. (FR-DV-04 does not specify a `sprk_optionsjson` payload — if the record requires non-null JSON, use `{}` or the minimal default per the existing DueDateCard chart-def authoring examples in the setup guide.)</step>
    <step order="5">Verify the record was created by issuing `mcp__dataverse__read_query` for the new record id.</step>
    <step order="6">Render verification: load a test Matter record with at least one upcoming `sprk_event` (finalduedate ≥ today) in the dev environment; place a Visual Host instance bound to this chart def on a temporary form; confirm it renders date + event title + days-from-now in the DueDateCard format (e.g., `May 28 / Pre-trial hearing · in 3d`).</step>
    <step order="7">Verify Drill Through: click expand on the rendered card; confirm it opens the `sprk_event` list filtered to upcoming for the current matter.</step>
    <step order="8">Update TASK-INDEX.md: 033 → ✅. Update current-task.md to next pending task.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="mcp__dataverse__create_record">Create the sprk_chartdefinition record</tool>
    <tool name="mcp__dataverse__read_query">Verify round-trip of FetchXML</tool>
